se Hildebrand <small>''until 15 May''</small>\n<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Ralph Pomeroy Buckland|Ralph P. Buckland]] <small>''until 16 May''</small>\n<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[James W. Denver]]<ref>[http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar;cc=moawar;idno=waro0010;node=waro0010%3A5;view=image;seq=764;size=100;page=root Denver's Official Report]</ref>\n|\n''Before 15 May''\n*[[53rd Ohio Infantry|53rd Ohio]]: Ltc Robert A. Fulton\n*57th Ohio: Ltc [[Americus V. Rice]]\n*77th Ohio: Ltc Wills De Haas\n''After 15 May''\n*[[48th Ohio Infantry|48th Ohio]]: Cpt Samuel G.W. Peterson\n*53rd Ohio: Col Wells Jones\n*[[70th Ohio Infantry|70th Ohio]]: Col [[Joseph R. Cockerill]]\n*[[72nd Ohio Infantry|72nd Ohio]]: Col Ralph P. Buckland\n|-\n| 4th Brigade\n<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Ralph P. Buckland\n|\n*[[48th Ohio Infantry|48th Ohio]]: Cpt Richard S. Robbins\n*70th Ohio: Col [[Joseph R. Cockerill]]\n*72nd Ohio: Cpt Charles G. Eaton\n''Discontinued 15 May''\n|-\n| Artillery\n<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nMaj Ezra Taylor\n|\n*[[Battery \"B\", 1st Regiment Illinois Volunteer Light Artillery|1st Illinois Artillery, Battery B]]: Cpt Samuel E. Barrett\n*[[Battery \"E\", 1st Regiment Illinois Volunteer Light Artillery|1st Illinois Artillery, Battery E]]: Lt John A. Fitch\n*[[Battery \"H\", 1st Regiment Illinois Volunteer Light Artillery|1st Illinois Artillery, Battery H]]: Cpt Axel Silverparre\n*1st Illinois Artillery, Battery I: Cpt Edward Bouton\n*[[4th Independent Battery Indiana Light Artillery|4th Indiana Battery]]: Lt William Mussman\n*[[7th Ohio Battery]]\n|-\n| Cavalry\n<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Theophilus Lyle Dickey|T. Lyle Dickey]]\n|\n*[[4th Regiment Illinois Volunteer Cavalry|4th Illinois Cavalry]], 2nd and 3rd Battalions: Col T. Lyle Dickey\n*[[Thielman's Independent Cavalry Battalion|Thielemann's Illinois Cavalry]], 2 companies: Maj Christian Thielemann\n|-\n| rowspan= 5 |\nSixth Division\n<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Thomas J. McKean]] <small>''until 30 Apr''</small><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG Thomas W. Sherman <small>''until 3 May''</small><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG Thomas J. McKean\n| 1st Brigade\n<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol John L. Doran <small>''until 23 May''</small><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[John McArthur]]\n|\n*[[21st Missouri Volunteer Infantry|21st Missouri]]: Col [[David Moore (military officer)|David Moore]]\n*[[25th Missouri Volunteer Infantry|25th Missouri]]: Ltc [[Robert T. Van Horn]]\n*[[16th Wisconsin Volunteer Infantry Regiment|16th Wisconsin]]: Maj Thomas Reynolds\n*[[17th Wisconsin Volunteer Infantry Regiment|17th Wisconsin]]: Col John L. Doran, Ltc [[Adam Gale Malloy|Adam G. Malloy]]\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[John M. Oliver]]\n|\n*[[15th Michigan Volunteer Infantry Regiment|15th Michigan]]: Maj Stephen Walsh\n*[[18th Missouri Volunteer Infantry|18th Missouri]]: Ltc John McDermott\n*[[18th Wisconsin Volunteer Infantry Regiment|18th Wisconsin]]: Cpt Charles H. Jackson\n*[[Independent Illinois Volunteer Cavalry Companies|Ford\u2019s Company Illinois Cavalry]]\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade\n<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Marcellus M. Crocker]]\n|\n* [[11th Iowa Volunteer Infantry Regiment|11th Iowa]]: Ltc William Hall\n* [[13th Iowa Volunteer Infantry Regiment|13th Iowa]]: Cpt George M. Van Hoesen\n* [[15th Iowa Volunteer Infantry Regiment|15th Iowa]]: Ltc William Dewey\n* [[16th Iowa Volunteer Infantry Regiment|16th Iowa]]: Ltc [[Addison H. Sanders]]\n|-\n| Artillery\n<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCpt [[Andrew Hickenlooper]]\n|\n*Battery F, 2nd Illinois Light Artillery: Lt Christian D. Bliss\n*[[1st Minnesota Light Artillery Battery|1st Minnesota Battery]]: Lt William Pfaender\n*[[3rd Ohio Battery]]: Cpt William S. Williams\n*[[5th Ohio Battery]]: Lt Lewis C. Sawyer\n*[[10th Ohio Battery]]: Cpt Hamilton B. White\n|-\n| Cavalry\n|\n*[[11th Regiment Illinois Volunteer Cavalry|11th Illinois Cavalry]], 1st and 2nd Battalions: Col [[Robert G. Ingersoll]]\n|}\n\n====Reserves (Army of the Tennessee)====\nMG [[John A. McClernand]]<ref>[http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar;cc=moawar;idno=waro0010;node=waro0010%3A5;view=image;seq=772;size=100;page=root McClernand's Official Report]</ref><ref>[http://digital.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar;cc=moawar;rgn=full%20text;idno=waro0011;didno=waro0011;view=image;seq=189;node=waro0011%3A1;page=root;size=100 Organization of the Right Wing, Left Wing and Reserve, in front of Corinth, MS, May 13, 1862]</ref>\n*Assistant Inspector General: Col [[Thomas E. G. Ransom]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! width=30% | Division\n! width=30% | Brigade\n! Regiments and Others\n|-\n| rowspan=5 |\nFirst Division\n<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nMG John A. McClernand <small>''until 2 May''</small><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[John A. Logan]] <small>''until 4 May''</small><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Henry M. Judah]] <small>''until 2 June''</small><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Thomas A. Davies]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG John A. Logan <small>''until 2 May''</small><ref>[http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar;cc=moawar;idno=waro0010;node=waro0010%3A5;view=image;seq=776;size=100;page=root Logan's Official Report]</ref><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Michael K. Lawler]] <small>''until 4 May''</small><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG John A. Logan\n|\n*[[8th Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment (3 Years)|8th Illinois]]: Ltc Frank L. Rhoads\n*[[18th Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|18th Illinois]]: Col [[Michael K. Lawler]]\n*[[30th Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|30th Illinois]]: Col [[Elias Dennis]]\n*[[31st Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|31st Illinois]]: Ltc Lyndorf Ozburn\n*[[12th Michigan Volunteer Infantry Regiment|12th Michigan]]: Col Francis Quinn\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[C. Carroll Marsh]] <small>''until 4 May''</small><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Andrew J. Babcock<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=OBkNAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA528&lpg=