10;node=waro0010%3A5;view=image;seq=731;size=100;page=root James D. Morgan's Official Report of the First Division]</ref>\n| 1st Brigade\n<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[John M. Palmer (politician)|John M. Palmer]]\n|\n*[[22nd Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|22nd Illinois]]: Ltc Harrison E. Hart\n*[[27th Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|27th Illinois]]: Ltc Fazilo Harrington\n*[[42nd Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|42nd Illinois]]: Col George W. Roberts\n*[[51st Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|51st Illinois]]: Col Gilbert W. Cumming\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[James D. Morgan]] <small>''until 1 May''</small>\n<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Daniel Tyler]]<ref>Dyer p. 477</ref>\n|\n*[[10th Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment (3 Year)|10th Illinois]]: Ltc John Tillson, Col [[James D. Morgan]]\n*[[16th Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|16th Illinois]]: Col Robert F. Smith\n*[[60th Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|60th Illinois]]: Col [[Silas C. Toler]]\n*[[10th Michigan Volunteer Infantry Regiment|10th Michigan]]: Col Charles M. Lum\n*[[14th Michigan Volunteer Infantry Regiment|14th Michigan]]: Col Robert P. Sinclair\n*[[64th Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|Yates\u2019 Sharpshooters]]: Ltc David E. Williams\n|-\n| Artillery\n|\n*[[Battery \"C\", 1st Regiment Illinois Volunteer Light Artillery|1st Illinois, Battery C]]\n*1st Missouri Artillery, Battery G\n|-\n| rowspan= 3 |\nSecond Division\n<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[David S. Stanley]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol John Groesbeck <small>''until 8 July''</small><ref>Dyer p. 477</ref><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Joseph L. Kirby Smith\n|\n*[[27th Ohio Infantry|27th Ohio]]: Col [[John W. Fuller]]\n*[[39th Ohio Infantry|39th Ohio]]: Col John Groesbeck, Ltc Alfred W. Gilbert\n*[[43rd Ohio Infantry|43rd Ohio]]: Col J.L. Kirby Smith\n*[[63rd Ohio Infantry|63rd Ohio]]: Col [[John W. Sprague]]\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Joseph B. Plummer]] <small>''until 29 May''</sma